ðŸ”¹ 1. Basics (Core Foundations)

What is Jenkins?

Open-source automation server for CI/CD.

Written in Java, extensible with plugins (1800+).

Automates build â†’ test â†’ deploy â†’ monitor pipelines.

Core Components

Job / Project â†’ unit of work (freestyle, pipeline, multibranch).

Build â†’ execution of a job.

Executor â†’ processing slot for a job.

Node / Agent â†’ machine running jobs.

Master / Controller â†’ orchestrates jobs, UI, scheduling.

Workspace â†’ directory where job runs.

Basic Workflow

Dev pushes code â†’ GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket.

Jenkins fetches code â†’ builds â†’ tests.

Artifacts â†’ Docker images, JAR/WAR, packages.

Deploy to servers â†’ Kubernetes, AWS, Azure.

Essential CLI Commands

jenkins-cli.jar -s http://localhost:8080 list-jobs
jenkins-cli.jar -s http://localhost:8080 build my-job
jenkins-cli.jar -s http://localhost:8080 get-job my-job
jenkins-cli.jar -s http://localhost:8080 create-job new-job < config.xml


âœ… Must-know foundation.

ðŸ”¹ 2. Medium-Level Concepts (Team Usage)

Types of Jobs

Freestyle Job â†’ quick setup, GUI-based.

Pipeline Job â†’ Jenkinsfile (Groovy DSL).

Multibranch Pipeline â†’ auto-detect branches/PRs.

Matrix Job â†’ build/test across OS/JDK versions.

Pipeline Types

Declarative Pipeline (preferred, structured).

Scripted Pipeline (flexible, Groovy-based).

Triggers

SCM Polling â†’ check repo every X minutes.

Webhooks â†’ GitHub/GitLab events.

Cron Scheduling â†’ scheduled builds.

Manual Triggers â†’ "Build Now" button.

Artifacts

Archive JAR/WAR/logs â†’ shared across builds.

Push artifacts to Nexus/Artifactory/S3.

Plugins (Must-Know)

Git, GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket.

Maven, Gradle, npm.

Docker, Kubernetes, Helm.

SonarQube, Checkstyle (code quality).

Slack, Email, Teams (notifications).

Credentials Management

Jenkins Credentials Store.

Types: username/password, SSH key, secret text, AWS keys.

Access via withCredentials{} in pipelines.

âœ… Daily Jenkins usage.

ðŸ”¹ 3. Advanced Concepts (FAANG-Level)

Pipeline Advanced

Stages & Steps â†’ build, test, deploy.

Parallel Stages â†’ speed up jobs.

Post Actions â†’ always, success, failure.

Shared Libraries â†’ reusable pipeline code across teams.

Dynamic Agents â†’ spin up Docker/Kubernetes agents on demand.

Scaling Jenkins

Master-Agent Architecture:

Master schedules jobs, agents execute.

Static agents (VMs, bare-metal).

Ephemeral agents (Docker, Kubernetes).

Cloud Auto-Scaling â†’ AWS EC2, Azure VMSS, GCP.

Security

RBAC (Role-Based Access Control).

Matrix Authorization â†’ fine-grained perms.

Masking Secrets in Console Output.

API Tokens instead of passwords.

Integrate Vault for external secrets.

Distributed Builds

Large projects â†’ split stages across agents.

Docker-in-Docker â†’ isolated builds.

Integration

CI â†’ automated tests (JUnit, pytest).

CD â†’ deploy with Ansible, Helm, Terraform.

GitOps â†’ Jenkins triggers ArgoCD/Flux.

High Availability (HA)

Backup JENKINS_HOME (jobs, configs, plugins).

Run Jenkins in Kubernetes with Operator.

HA â†’ multiple controllers + external DB.

Observability

Integrate with Prometheus + Grafana (Jenkins Exporter).

Centralized logs â†’ ELK/EFK stack.

Notifications â†’ Slack/MS Teams.

âœ… These topics separate juniors from seniors.

ðŸ”¹ 4. Real-World DevOps Scenarios

End-to-End CI/CD â†’ Jenkins pipeline builds Docker image, pushes to ECR/GCR, deploys to EKS with Helm.

Blue-Green Deployment â†’ Jenkins pipeline swaps traffic between old/new versions.

Canary Release â†’ partial rollout with monitoring.

Security Scans â†’ Jenkins + SonarQube + Trivy + OWASP.

Secrets Management â†’ Jenkins + Vault/SSM.

Pipeline as Code â†’ Jenkinsfile in Git repo.

Multi-Branch Pipelines â†’ auto-build PRs.

GitHub Actions + Jenkins â†’ Actions for tests, Jenkins for infra.

Cost Optimization â†’ dynamic Kubernetes agents.

Disaster Recovery â†’ restore from backup, rebuild plugins.

âœ… These are production-grade practices.

ðŸ”¹ 5. Extra Advanced (Rare but Asked)

Jenkins X â†’ Kubernetes-native Jenkins.

Terraform + Jenkins â†’ IaC automation.

Jenkinsfile Best Practices

Small reusable steps.

Fail fast with set -e.

Use parallel where possible.

Audit Logs â†’ security compliance.

Pipeline Libraries â†’ versioned Groovy libraries.

